              When we handle documentation as part of our truck management
              services, we do not simply complete and file the document and
              leave it at that. We understand how important the different
              aspects of your documentation is for you and your business. With
              this in mind, we keep track of all the different provisions
              covered in your trucking business documents and work with you to
              confirm that these provisions have been fulfilled.
            </p>
            <br />
            <p>
              For example, you may be required to complete certain details or
              requirements laid out in your customer agreements. These may
              include providing critical handling directions to the shipper or
              consignee or scheduling shipping appointments and other
              time-sensitive considerations. With Logity Dispatch on your side,
              you gain the peace of mind that comes from knowing these
              requirements are being met without fail.
            </p>
            <br />
            <h2>Document Dispatch</h2>
